{"id":61552,"title":"Self-management of chronic oedema in the community.","abstract":"The number of people living with long-term conditions in the UK is increasing. This is putting an immense strain on already stretched health and social care resources. Government strategies are aimed at encouraging and supporting self-management of these conditions. Self-management of chronic oedema has always been a key aspect of care planning for this patient group. This article focuses on how nurses can encourage and support self-management in chronic oedema. ","date":"2014-04-07","categories":"Hemic and Lymphatic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24704752","annotations":[{"name":"Health","weight":0.793294,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health"},{"name":"Government","weight":0.762749,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Government"},{"name":"Social work","weight":0.739625,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social_work"},{"name":"Community","weight":0.579766,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Community"},{"name":"Health care","weight":0.545277,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Health_care"},{"name":"United Kingdom","weight":0.497399,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Kingdom"},{"name":"Social","weight":0.462262,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Social"},{"name":"Resource","weight":0.359054,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resource"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.162218,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Strategy","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strategy"},{"name":"Nurse","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nurse"},{"name":"Planning","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planning"},{"name":"Chronic (medicine)","weight":0.0508378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chronic_(m